# Railway/Docker build context for the Toast-86 cron (see Dockerfile).
# The cron build needs ONLY scripts/sync-toast-86-attribution.mjs and installs
# firebase-admin directly, so keep the build context tiny — shipping the whole
# repo (src, the Capacitor android/ios native projects, functions, etc.) made
# "sending build context" slow and the build appear stuck.
node_modules
dist
.git
.github
src
public
android
ios
functions
docs
icons
assets
pi-tv-setup
pi5-print-bridge
e2e
.vscode
*.log
.DS_Store
# Never ship the Firestore admin credential into a build context.
firebase-service-account.json
